com.nimbusds.openid.connect.claims
Class ClientAuthenticationClaims

java.lang.Object
  com.nimbusds.openid.connect.claims.JSONObjectClaims
      com.nimbusds.openid.connect.claims.ClientAuthenticationClaims

public class ClientAuthenticationClaims
extends JSONObjectClaims

Client authentication claims, serialisable to a JSON object. Used for client secret JWT and private key JWT authentication at the Token endpoint.

Note that OpenID Connect mandates the use the jti claim, see https://bitbucket.org/openid/connect/issue/583/messages-221-client-auth-claims-not

Example client authentication claims set: 

 {
   "iss" : "http://client.example.com",
   "prn" : "http://client.example.com",
   "aud" : "http://server.example.com",
   "jti" : "d396036d-c4d9-40d8-8e98-f7e8327002d9",
   "exp" : 1311281970,
   "iat" : 1311280970
 }

See http://openid.net/specs/openid-connect-messages-1_0.html#client_authentication

See draft-jones-oauth-jwt-bearer-04

Version:
0.9 (2012-05-11)
Author:
Vladimir Dzhuvinov

Constructor Detail

ClientAuthenticationClaims

public ClientAuthenticationClaims(Issuer iss,
                                  Principal prn,
                                  Audience aud,
                                  JWTID jti,
                                  ExpirationTime exp)
Creates a new minimal client authentication claims instance. Use the setter methods for the optional claims.

Parameters:
iss - The issuer. Must contain the client_id of the OAuth client. Must not be null.
prn - The principal. Must contain the client_id of the OAuth client. Must not be null.
aud - The audience, typically the URL of the authorisation server's token endpoint. Must not be null.
jti - The unique identifier for the JWT. The JWT ID may be used by implementations requiring message de-duplication for one-time use assertions.
exp - The expiration time. Must not be null.
